The paper presents an approach for automatically repairing bugs in software programs, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The approach involves using Satisfiability Modulo Theory (SMT), which is a technique used in programming languages (cs.PL) and automated reasoning (cs.AI). The paper also mentions repairing object-oriented code, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the approach involves transforming data into a problem that can be solved using SMT solvers, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
